content: Easily THE best app for learning JavaScript or even relearning (as I am). Short and informative text and excellent "try it yourself" examples. I'd recommend this app to anyone trying to learn JavaScript or trying to refresh skills. (I'd recommend HTML & CSS too!) Buying the pro version was a no brainier, we need more programming apps like these!! Only note is to make it able to transfer data (quiz completion) to another phone (recently changed phones and had to do it all over again)

This app feels very polished unlike a lot of these learning apps. It has a full series of lessons which are complete but fairly succinct. The "try it" emulator seems pretty solid too. Very much worth a buck and a half!
The layout is perfect and distraction free. I started with the free version and bought JS, CSS, and HTML pro because I was so impressed
Cool
Great lessons, easy to modify exercise programs, wish the tests were a little harder but that nitpicking. I'm a third of the way through and hoping the remainder will be extremely useful.
Amazing app with almost best feature for beginners also. Love it.

I'm still fairly new to programming but have used other apps to start learning Javascript and web development. To me, this app does the best in presenting the information in a way that's easy to understand and follow. I also recommend the CSS and HTML apps by Codeliber.
Simply amazing way to learn JS on the go!
Very good app to learn JavaScript
Really easy to learn from. Good platform can't say enough good about it

I've just started with it. Had a minor glitch with the purchase not being visible/applied at the level of my Google account initially. After less than 12 hours this was addressed and I managed to install the app on a secondary device. Overall, I am happy. I'll see how this goes and update my review, if needed. Learn away! :)
Best app
Can you make a visualisation which will show what topic user has already done?
replyContent:
Hello Maxim, thank you for the review.

Regarding your question, you can check out the "Quiz / Learning Progress" page from the menu bar to see the topics and the associated quizzes that you have already done.

If you have more questions, please don't hesitate to contact me at thecodeliber@gmail.com.

Thank you very much.

Great app. I've also purchased the html and css apps. The content is awesome. The only problems I have with these apps is there is no dark mode in the lessons (there is in the editor) and the hamburger menu is not accessible by a left swipe. I need to click on it in the top left corner which can be a reach on large screen phones. Also, it would be great if the lessons can be navigated by swipes in addition to left and right arrows at the bottom.
Best for those who want to learn without internet connection. It is very simple, very lightweight and so great app for learning to code JavaScript.
Great app.

The most addictive programming learning app of all times!! It's simple but very direct and straight to the point. I have already bought all this developer's programming learning app and I cannot wait for the next ones still!! Which one will it be? PHP, Python, SQL, Java, Kotlin...?
